org.apache.xpath.composite

Class SequenceTypeSupport

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.xpath.composite.SequenceTypeSupport

  • public class SequenceTypeSupport
extends java.lang.Object
    This class provides few utility methods, to support evaluation of XPath 3.1 sequence type expressions.

    • Method Detail

      • castXDMValueToAnotherType

        public static XObject castXDMValueToAnotherType(XObject srcValue,
                                                java.lang.String sequenceTypeXPathExprStr,
                                                SequenceTypeData seqExpectedTypeDataInp,
                                                XPathContext xctxt,
                                                java.util.List prefixTable)
                                         throws javax.xml.transform.TransformerException
        This method casts an XPath 3.1 xdm source value represented by an XObject object instance, to a value of another xdm data type. For XPath sequence type expressions that represent KindTest (i.e, element(), attribute() etc), this method only checks whether an XML input item conforms with the provided KindTest sequence type expression, and returns an input value unchanged.
        Parameters:
        srcValue - an XObject object instance that represents a source xdm value
        sequenceTypeXPathExprStr - an XPath sequence type expression string
        seqExpectedTypeDataInp - an XPath sequence type compiled expression
        xctxt - the current XPath context object
        prefixTable - an XSLT transformation run-time XML namespace bindings prefix table
        Returns:
        an XObject object instance produced, as a result of data type conversion performed by this method on an object instance srcValue.
        Throws:
        javax.xml.transform.TransformerException
